%I A397481 #7 Jul 03 2026 22:46:39
%S A397481 24,136,384,538,664,864,1048,1192
%N A397481 Integers x such that there exist four integers 0<y<=z<=t<=w such that sigma(x)*psi(x)^3 = x^4 + y^4 + z^4 + t^4 + w^4.
%C A397481 The numbers x, y, z, t and w form a sigma*psi^3-quartic quintuple.
%H A397481 S. I. Dimitrov, <a href="https://hal.science/hal-05303937">On σψ-quadratic k-tuples and related generalizations</a>, hal-05303937, 2025.
%H A397481 S. I. Dimitrov, <a href="https://github.com/Stoyan16/Sigma-psi-3-quartic-quintuples/blob/main/A397481">Python program</a> (GitHub)
%e A397481 (136, 68, 76, 156, 204) is such a quintuple because sigma(136) * psi(136)^3 = 270 * 216^3 = 136^4 + 68^4 + 76^4 + 156^4 + 204^4.
%o A397481 (Python) # See Links.
%Y A397481 Cf. A000203, A001615, A386225, A391536, A397304, A397440.
%K A397481 nonn,hard,more,new
%O A397481 1,1
